summaries.short: Barb, Nicki and Margene mull over custody scenarios; Bill is recruited by an influential civic group.
summaries.full: The Henricksons' public stock is rising, as Barb finds herself a finalist for Mother of the Year and Bill is asked to become the newest member of the Salt Lake City Leadership League. Meanwhile, the three wives mull over custody scenarios in their separate wills, but are chastened for their subterfuge when Hatcher tells Bill.

summaries.short: In the Season One finale, Wanda causes more trouble with Roman, and Barb attends the Mother of the Year ceremony.
summaries.full: In the Season One finale, Bill and Joey blindside Roman at a UEB Priesthood Council meeting--but will their triumph be short-lived? Wanda's bad habits resurface during a visit from Alby; Adaleen puts an end to Rhonda's thespian sabbatical; Nicki's family allegiances are tested; and Barb seizes the spotlight at the Mother of the Year award ceremony.

summaries.short: Bill and family plan for Teenie's baptism; Bill attempts to infiltrate Roman's UEB Council.
summaries.full: Barb gets an unwanted visit from her sister Cindy, who disapproves of the family's lifestyle. Meanwhile, as his feud with Roman intensifies, Bill seeks to infiltrate the UEB Priesthood Council. Ben gives Brynn a token of his affection, and is offered a much more significant one in return. A depressed Margene is transformed at Teenie's baptism.

summaries.full: A crisis leads Bill to rethink Home Plus's ad strategy. Joey is caught between a rock and a hard place, driving him to fall off the wagon and sending Nicki (accompanied by Margene) on a remedial trip to the compound. In the midst of crises, Bill and Barb forget Nicki's anniversary, and Joey makes a decision that will have far-ranging implications.

summaries.short: Bill's household gets a lot more crowded; Franklin indulges his bad habits; Roman is surprised by Bill's new offer.
summaries.full: Having been evicted from their temporary lodgings, Franklin, his wives and dog descend on Bill's just in time for Easter--as does Joey, who's looking for a fresh start. Meanwhile, Bill finds himself drowning in lawsuits; Nicki learns she's not alone in debt; Sarah unexpectedly bonds with Lois; and Bill surprises Roman with a final settlement offer.
